<item>
 <title>Multimedia at the Command Line</title>
 <link>https://www.socallinuxexpo.org/scale9x/presentations/multimedia-command-line</link>
 <description>&lt;p&gt;Survey of command line tools available in any console for handling multimedia from the raw console&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;field field-type-text field-field-track&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;
            &lt;div class=&quot;field-item odd&quot;&gt;
                &lt;a href=&quot;category/presentationcategory/general&quot;&gt;General&lt;/a&gt;        &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;field field-type-text field-field-presentation-short-abs&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;
            &lt;div class=&quot;field-item odd&quot;&gt;
                &lt;p&gt;We frequently think of multimedia on Linux as being a collection of X applications, but there is much that can be done from almost any console.  This presentation will survey multimedia tools usable at a Linux console, giving examples and tips along the way.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;field field-type-text field-field-presentation-long-abs&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;
            &lt;div class=&quot;field-item odd&quot;&gt;
                &lt;p&gt;We frequently think of multimedia on Linux as being a collection of X applications, but there is much that can be done from almost any console. These tools can be used for many reasons, varying from usability/accessability issues, problems that fall through the cracks or are corner cases of GUI front ends and tools, squeezing performance out of low end, light weight or embedded  equipment, or just getting more feel for what&#039;s going on. This presentation will survey multimedia tools usable at a raw Linux console, giving examples and tips along the way. If time permits, we&#039;ll go over some use cases I&#039;ve encountered.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;field field-type-text field-field-presentation-speaker-id&quot;&gt;
