<item>
 <title>Herding Cat5</title>
 <link>https://www.socallinuxexpo.org/scale9x/presentations/herding-cat5</link>
 <description>&lt;p&gt;Keeping the infrastructure maintainable&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;field field-type-text field-field-track&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;
            &lt;div class=&quot;field-item odd&quot;&gt;
                &lt;a href=&quot;special-events/devops-day-los-angeles&quot;&gt;DevOps&lt;/a&gt;        &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;field field-type-text field-field-presentation-short-abs&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;
            &lt;div class=&quot;field-item odd&quot;&gt;
                &lt;p&gt;Most DevOps organizations have systems configuration management in place, but not many have begun to automate their network. In this session Edmunds will present on how their DevOps organization has started to automate network configuration with an open-source framework that exposes content routing and load balancer management to web applications.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;field field-type-text field-field-presentation-long-abs&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;
            &lt;div class=&quot;field-item odd&quot;&gt;
                &lt;p&gt;Most DevOps organizations have systems configuration management in place, but not many have begun to automate their network. In this session Edmunds will present on how their DevOps organization has started to automate network configuration with an open-source framework that exposes content routing and load balancer management to web applications.&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
